cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper discusses the use of convolutional neural networks (CNNs) for image processing, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The paper also discusses strategies for reducing overfitting, which is a common topic in machine learning (cs.LG). The use of preset filters and the comparison to wavelets suggests a focus on signal processing (cs.MM) and specifically on the use of Fourier transforms (cs.NE) and/or other mathematical techniques (cs.AI) for image processing.
